<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,682]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
1. Metope smooth, without distinct intermediate carinae (
<figureCitation box="[755,817,220,242]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1230,1254]" captionTargetBox="[152,1417,201,1225]" captionTargetId="figure-334@3.[151,1435,179,1239]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Lethierium reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), male, Mékalis. 1—dorsal view; 2—lateral view; 3—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[829,842,220,241]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[182,1420,678,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-251@5.[151,1435,669,1717]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 6–8. Lethierium juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), female, Aïn Kerma. 6—dorsal view; 7—lateral view; 8—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[853,878,220,241]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,788,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-298@6.[151,1436,776,1701]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 9—dorsal view; 10—lateral view; 11—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[889,916,220,242]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[161,1406,181,1236]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,1266]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., 12–14—holotype, 15—female paratype, Marrakech. 12—dorsal view; 13, 15—lateral view; 14—frontal view.Abbreviation: kp — knee prominence. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">14</figureCitation>
). Each forewing with distinct shoulder-shaped prominence (or knee prominence) well visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[766,827,249,271]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1230,1254]" captionTargetBox="[152,1417,201,1225]" captionTargetId="figure-334@3.[151,1435,179,1239]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Lethierium reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), male, Mékalis. 1—dorsal view; 2—lateral view; 3—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[839,853,249,271]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[182,1420,678,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-251@5.[151,1435,669,1717]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 6–8. Lethierium juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), female, Aïn Kerma. 6—dorsal view; 7—lateral view; 8—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[863,877,250,271]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,788,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-298@6.[151,1436,776,1701]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 9—dorsal view; 10—lateral view; 11—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[887,912,250,272]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[161,1406,181,1236]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,1266]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., 12–14—holotype, 15—female paratype, Marrakech. 12—dorsal view; 13, 15—lateral view; 14—frontal view.Abbreviation: kp — knee prominence. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">12</figureCitation>
).......................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,682]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
- Metope with distinct median and sublateral carinae (
<figureCitation box="[729,804,279,301]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,273,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-86@8.[151,1435,273,1500]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 16—dorsal view; 17—lateral view; 18—frontal view; 19—caudal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">Figs 18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[814,841,279,301]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–55" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,191,1534]" captionTargetId="figure-28@16.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 53–55. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 53—face; 54—eye, scapus, pedicel, and paranotal lobe, frontal view; 55—head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">53</figureCitation>
). Forewings with weak knee prominences (
<figureCitation box="[1257,1329,279,301]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,273,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-86@8.[151,1435,273,1500]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Lethierium carinatum sp. nov., female paratype, Bou Naceur. 16—dorsal view; 17—lateral view; 18—frontal view; 19—caudal view. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[1346,1433,279,300]" name="Morocco" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">Morocco</collectingCountry>
................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Gnezdilov, 2022" authorityName="Gnezdilov" authorityYear="2022" box="[1230,1354,309,330]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1230,1354,309,330]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">L. carinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1360,1436,308,329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1436,308,329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,682]" box="[151,1436,337,359]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,337,359]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">2. Hind tibia with a single lateral spine...................................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,682]" box="[151,1436,367,389]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,367,389]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">- Hind tibia with two lateral spines......................................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,682]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
3. Phallobase basement with large lobe-shaped processes (
<figureCitation box="[762,834,396,418]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–29" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1599,1623]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,185,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-28@10.[171,1415,181,1575]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 23–29. Lethierium reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), Aïn Sefra, male genitalia. 23—pygofer, lateral view; 24—anal tube, dorsal view; 25—anal tube, lateral view; 26—penis and connective, lateral view; 27—penis, ventral view; 28—style, dorsal view; 29—style, lateral view. Out of scale." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with nearly straight ventral hooks. 
<collectingCountry box="[1283,1355,396,418]" name="Algeria" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">Algeria</collectingCountry>
.................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lethierry, 1878)" baseAuthorityName="Lethierry" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[1177,1436,425,448]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Hysteropterum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reiberi">
<emphasis box="[1177,1266,425,447]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">L. reiberi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lethierry, M. L." box="[1279,1429,425,448]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519" pagination="25 - 31" refId="ref9505" refString="Lethierry, M. L. (1878) Homopteres nouveaux d'Europe et des contrees voisines. Pt. 2. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 21, 25 - 31." type="journal article" year="1878">Lethierry, 1878</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,682]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
- Phallobase basement with short lobe-shaped processes (
<figureCitation box="[773,847,455,477]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–38" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1482,1506]" captionTargetBox="[174,1429,254,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-250@12.[151,1436,224,1437]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 32–38. Lethierium juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, male genitalia. 32 – pygofer, lateral view; 33 – penis, ven- tral view; 34 – penis and connective, lateral view; 35 – style, lateral view; 36 – style, dorsal view; 37 – anal tube, dorsal view; 38 – anal tube, lateral view. Out of scale." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with strongly curved ventral hooks. 
<collectingCountry box="[1322,1394,455,477]" name="Algeria" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">Algeria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[226,313,485,506]" name="Morocco" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">Morocco</collectingCountry>
....................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bergevin, 1915)" baseAuthorityName="Bergevin" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[1165,1436,484,506]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juniperi">
<emphasis box="[1165,1267,485,506]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">L. juniperi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bergevin" box="[1279,1429,484,506]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519" pagination="71 - 77" refId="ref8660" refString="Bergevin, de E. (1915) Description de deux espece nouvelles d' Hysteropterum (Hemipt., Issidae) de l'Afrique du Nord. Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord, 7, 71 - 77." type="journal article" year="1915">Bergevin, 1915</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,682]" pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="519">
4. Metope with straight upper margin (
<figureCitation box="[575,648,513,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[161,1406,181,1236]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,1266]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., 12–14—holotype, 15—female paratype, Marrakech. 12—dorsal view; 13, 15—lateral view; 14—frontal view.Abbreviation: kp — knee prominence. Scale bar—1 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="519">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
